Check effects of adjustment

files <- list.files("out/disease_each/", pattern = "res.rmp.rds") %>% paste0("out/disease_each/", .)

df <- c()
for(i in files){
  temp <- read_rds(i)
  df <- rbind(df, temp)
}
df <- df %>% filter(case_n > 50) %>% filter(cont_n > 50)
df$name <- df$name %>% str_replace("species incertae sedis", "sp.")
r_max <- max(df$rel_disease, df$rel_load)
df$col <- ifelse(df$fdr > 0.1, "ns", ifelse(df$e > 0, "enriched", "depleted"))

## plot species that lost their significance
target.list <- c("Crohn's disease", "Ulcerative colitis", "Liver cirrhosis", "IBS-D", "C.difficile infection", "Slow transit constipation")

df.all <- c()
plot.list <- list()
count <- 0
for(target in target.list){
  df2 <- df %>% filter(disease == target) %>% filter(name != "Shannon diversity")
  temp <- df2 %>% filter(fdr < 0.05 & fdr_adj > 0.05) %>% arrange(fdr) %>% head(n = 20)

  temp1 <- temp %>% select(name, fdr, e, disease) %>% mutate(data = "Before", fdr = fdr, e = e)
  temp2 <- temp %>% select(name, fdr = fdr_adj, e = e_adj, disease) %>% mutate(data = "After")
  
  df2 <- rbind(temp1, temp2)
  df2$data <- factor(df2$data, levels = c("Before", "After"))

  df2$name <- df2$name %>% str_replace("species incertae sedis", "sp.")
  p <- ggplot(df2, aes(y = reorder(name, log10(fdr), min), x = -log10(fdr))) +
    theme_mine() +
    geom_point(aes(col = data)) +
    geom_path(col = "black", arrow = arrow(length=unit(0.15,"cm"), type = "closed"), size = 0.2, aes(group = name)) +
    ggtitle(target) +
    ggforestplot::geom_stripes(odd = "#80808010", even = "#00000000") +
    theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(colour = "gray80", size = 0.2)) +
    scale_color_manual(values = c(dj_2[5], dj[5])) +  
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
    xlab("-log10(FDR)") +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5, size = 8)) +
    theme(axis.text.y = element_text(size = 8), axis.title.y = element_text(size = 8)) +    
    theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
    geom_vline(xintercept = -log10(0.05), col = "red", linetype = 2) +
    coord_flip()
  p %>% print()
  
  count <- count + 1
}

Compare adjustments between measured and predicted microbial loads (liver cirrhosis)

## GALAXY/MicrobLiver (liver cirrhosis)
model <- read_rds("out/model/model_metacardis.motus25.rds")
model <- model[[1]]

## read mOTUs
d <- data.table::fread("data/formatted/GALAXY_mOTUs25.tsv") %>% data.frame(check.names = F)
rownames(d) <- d[, 1]
d <- d[, -1]

## select ALD patients and healthy individuals
keep <- rownames(d) %>% str_detect("ALD|HP")
d <- d[keep, ]

## metadata
md <- read.delim("data/formatted/GALAXY_metadata_nr.tsv", header = T)
md2 <- read.delim("data/formatted/GALA-ALD.kleiner.tsv", header = T)
md <- left_join(md, md2, by = "ID")

keep1 <- rownames(d) %in% md$ID
keep2 <- md$ID %in% rownames(d)
d <- d[keep1, ]
md <- md[keep2, ]

## use only advanced stage patients
keep <- md$kleiner == "3" | md$kleiner == "4" | is.na(md$kleiner)
d <- d[keep, ]
md <- md[keep, ]

## predict microbial load
d.min <- min(d[d != 0])/2
d$`Shannon diversity` <- diversity(d)
md$predicted_count <- predict(model, scale(log10(d + d.min)))
## [19:38:42] WARNING: src/learner.cc:1203: 
##   If you are loading a serialized model (like pickle in Python, RDS in R) generated by
##   older XGBoost, please export the model by calling `Booster.save_model` from that version
##   first, then load it back in current version. See:
## 
##     https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/saving_model.html
## 
##   for more details about differences between saving model and serializing.
## 
## [19:38:42] WARNING: src/learner.cc:888: Found JSON model saved before XGBoost 1.6, please save the model using current version again. The support for old JSON model will be discontinued in XGBoost 2.3.
## [19:38:42] WARNING: src/learner.cc:553: 
##   If you are loading a serialized model (like pickle in Python, RDS in R) generated by
##   older XGBoost, please export the model by calling `Booster.save_model` from that version
##   first, then load it back in current version. See:
## 
##     https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/latest/tutorials/saving_model.html
## 
##   for more details about differences between saving model and serializing.
md$count <- md$count %>% log10()

keep <- apply(d, 2, mean) > 1E-4 & apply(d > 0, 2, mean) > 0.1
d <- d[, keep]

colnames(d) <- colnames(d) %>% str_remove("ref_mOTU_v25_") %>% str_remove("meta_mOTU_v25_")

## number of patients
md$md <- md$ID %>% str_detect("ALD")

md$md2 <- ifelse(md$md == T, "Liver cirrhosis", "Control")
gal1 <- data.frame(id = md$ID, count = md$count, md = md$md2, data = "Mesured load", cohort = "GALAXY/MicrobLiver")
gal2 <- data.frame(id = md$ID, count = md$predicted_count, md = md$md2, data = "Predicted load", cohort = "GALAXY/MicrobLiver")
df.gal <- rbind(gal1, gal2)

p <- c()
e <- c()
p_adj <- c()
e_adj <- c()
p_adj2 <- c()
e_adj2 <- c()
for(i in 1:ncol(d)){
  md$y <- log10(d[, i] + 1E-4)
  res <- glm(y ~ md + Age + Sex + BMI, data = md) %>% summary()
  res_adj <- glm(y ~ md + Age + Sex + BMI + count, data = md) %>% summary()
  res_adj2 <- glm(y ~ md + Age + Sex + BMI + predicted_count, data = md) %>% summary()  
  
  p[i] <- res$coefficients[2, 4]
  e[i] <- res$coefficients[2, 1]  
  
  p_adj[i] <- res_adj$coefficients[2, 4]
  e_adj[i] <- res_adj$coefficients[2, 1]  
  
  p_adj2[i] <- res_adj2$coefficients[2, 4]
  e_adj2[i] <- res_adj2$coefficients[2, 1]  
}
df <- data.frame(name = colnames(d), 
                 e = e, p = p, fdr = p.adjust(p, method = "fdr"), 
                 e_adj = e_adj, p_adj = p_adj, fdr_adj = p.adjust(p_adj, method = "fdr"),
                 e_adj2 = e_adj2, p_adj2 = p_adj2, fdr_adj2 = p.adjust(p_adj2, method = "fdr")
                 )

df$delta <- log10(df$fdr) - log10(df$fdr_adj)
df$delta2 <- log10(df$fdr) - log10(df$fdr_adj2)

p1 <- ggplot(df, aes(x = delta, y = delta2)) +
  theme_mine() +
  ggpubr::stat_cor() +
  ggtitle("Liver cirrhosis (GALAXY/MicrobLiver)") +
  xlab("Change in FDR due to adjustments\nfor measured loads") +
  ylab("Change in FDR due to adjustments\nfor predicted loads") +  
  geom_abline(slope = 1, col = "gray", linetype = 2) +
  ggrastr::geom_point_rast(alpha = 0.6, size = 1, col = "gray") +  
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = T) 
p1
## `geom_smooth()` using formula = 'y ~ x'

Compare FDR of top species (liver cirrhosis)

res1 <- df %>% arrange(-delta) %>% tail(n = 21) %>% select(name, fdr, fdr_adj, delta) %>% gather("keys", "value", -name, -delta) %>% mutate(adjustment = "Measuread load")
res2 <- df %>% arrange(-delta) %>% tail(n = 21) %>% select(name, fdr, fdr_adj2, delta2) %>% gather("keys", "value", -name, -delta2) %>% mutate(adjustment = "Predicted load")
colnames(res2) <- colnames(res2) %>% str_replace("delta2", "delta")
res <- rbind(res1, res2)

res$value <- res$value %>% log10()
res$value <- -res$value

res$delta[res$keys != "fdr"] <- 0
res$shape <- ifelse(res$keys == "fdr", 1, 2) %>% factor()

res$cate <- res$name %>% str_detect("Shannon")
res$name <- res$name %>% str_replace("species incertae sedis ", "sp. ")

p2 <- ggplot(res, aes(x = reorder(name, -value, mean), y = value, col = adjustment, group = adjustment, fill = adjustment)) +
  theme_mine() +
  ggtitle("Liver cirrhosis (GALAXY/MicrobLiver)") +
  ylim(c(0, 23)) +
  theme(panel.grid.major.y = element_line(color = "gray90")) +
  ylab("FDR(-log10)") +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(0.05), linetype = 2) +
  geom_point(aes(shape = shape), position = position_dodge(width = 0.5), stroke = 0, size = 2) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymax = value, ymin = value + delta, col = adjustment), position = position_dodge(width = 0.5), width = 0) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = c(16, 25), labels = c("Before adjustment", "After adjustment")) +
  scale_color_manual(values = tidy_col) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = tidy_col) +  
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, vjust = 0.5)) +
  theme(strip.text.x = element_blank()) +
  facet_grid(~cate, space = "free", scales = "free")

## MetaCardis (T2D)
model <- read_rds("out/model/model_galaxy.motus25.rds")
model <- model[[1]]

## read mOTUs

rownames(d) <- d[, 1]
d <- d[, -1]

## read metadata
md <- read.delim("data/formatted/MetaCardis_metadata.tsv", header = T)
md <- md %>% filter(PATGROUPFINAL_C == 3 | PATGROUPFINAL_C == 8)

keep1 <- rownames(d) %in% md$id
keep2 <- md$id %in% rownames(d)
d <- d[keep1, ]
md <- md[keep2, ]

## predict microbial load

Comparing microbial loads between cases and controls

df <- rbind(df.gal, df.mc)
df$md <- df$md %>% str_replace("T2D", "Type 2 diabetes")
df$md2 <- ifelse(df$md == "Control", "Control", "Case")

pair <- list()
pair[[1]] <- c("Case", "Control")

p.comp <- ggplot(df, aes(x = md2, group = md2, y = count, fill = data)) +
  theme_mine() +
  ylab("Microbial load (log10)") +
  geom_boxplot(aes(y = count, group = md2, x = md2)) +
  facet_grid(~ cohort + data, scales = "free") +  
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, vjust = 1)) +
  theme(axis.title.x = element_blank()) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank()) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = tidy_col) +
  ggpubr::stat_compare_means(tip.length = 0, comparisons = pair, size = 2) 
p.comp
